cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.CL, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the application of automated theorem provers to improve the competency of FOL ontologies for commonsense reasoning tasks. This topic is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it uses WordNet for benchmarking. Additionally, the paper deals with the evaluation of different formulations of the Closed World Assumption, which is a concept in database systems (cs.DB) and knowledge representation (cs.KR). Finally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation, which are common in software engineering (cs.SE).
